'''Yang Wood Dog also known as 甲戌''' (kinoe inu, kouboku no inu, koujutsu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 11th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Guiyou|ja|癸酉}} and followed by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|乙亥}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Dog|ja|戌}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）}}) (Wood overcomes Earth).  
