It is the 11th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Guiyou|ja|癸酉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|乙亥|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Dog|ja|戌|1=Dog (zodiac)|lt=Dog (戌)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) (Wood overcomes Earth).  
