'''Yang Wood Dog also known as 甲戌''' (kinoe inu, kouboku no inu, koujutsu) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

It is the 11th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Guiyou|ja|癸酉|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Otsugai|ja|乙亥|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Kou|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft}} symbol {{ill|Dog|ja|戌|1=Dog (zodiac)|lt=Dog (戌)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, establishing a restraining relationship ({{ill|Mutual Restraint|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) (Wood overcomes Earth).  
